attles over what policy instructions are authoritative. The book encourages readers to connect the dots of British statecraft, and to understand how, exactly, public demands are transferred into laws that are then implemented with greater and lesser degrees of success. Crucially, it shows that vague legislation has a tremendous impact on policy delivery, disproportionately affecting the weakest, in areas including immigration, homelessness and anti-discrimination.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBill draftingzGreat Britain. 0aConstitutional lawzGreat Britain. 0aLawxLanguage. 0aLegislationzGreat Britain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831111966640 cprintz978152920020140uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529200218?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529200218423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529200218/original  a978-3-11-119666-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles